 the world in applied informatics—turning big data into smart insights for transportation and agriculture by using machine learning to extract the information engineers and scientists need to solve complex problems we’re making our roads safer and our farms smarter building better communities today means we’re creating a better world tomorrow iteris provides products services and solutions to improve the efficiency of farms and roads in  countries to help communities throughout the world optimize crop yield and keep their roads safe company details  carnegie avenue  santa ana  california  usa locations served business type manufacturer industry type monitoring and testing market focus globally various continents about us iteris the iteris logo abacus clearpath weather edge iperform ipems smartcycle smartspan vantage vantage next next and vantage vector are registered trademarks of iteris inc registered with the us patent and trademark office and in several additional countries as applicable mission our mission is to be the leading intelligent traffic management information company applying advanced technologies to plan design integrate and enable complete solutions that address significant needs in the traffic management market we commit ourselves to high standards of integrity in contributing to the best interests of our clients the transportation profession our associates and our communities and to seeking significant returns to our shareholders based on the continual pursuit of technological and operational excellence history iteris’ roots date back to  when engineers used their video image processing expertise to introduce vantage iteris’ first commercial vehicle detection product to address the intelligent transportation systems its market in the late s iteris acquired the transportation systems business of rockwell international corp meyer mohaddes associates a premier traffic engineering and its consulting firm based in los angeles and certain assets of the washington dcbased consulting firm of viggen corporation to enhance our product engineering and its consulting practices  at the same time iteris developed and went into production with the world’s first commercially available lane departure warning ldw system which was soon deployed on commercial trucks in europe and the us within four years the first passenger cars to offer ldw became available in the us  iteris continued to mature alongside the its industry since the early s and has emerged as a flourishing company with distinguished products and services that have resulted in national projects and awards  in  iteris divested its lane departure product group to focus and transform into an intelligent traffic management information company later that year we established the iperform group to develop and market software based performance measurement and management products and services we acquired meridian environmental technologies providing us with added expertise in traveler information systems as well as weather forecasting and information system we also acquired berkeley transportation systems with expertise in performance measurement and management  our products and services range from regional and statewide traffic management programs to commercial vehicle operations contracts and goods movement programs to a comprehensive offering of roadway detection products serving both public and commercial customers in providing predictive traffic and weather information systems with corporate headquarters in santa ana california and over  offices nationwide as well as south america and middle east the company remains committed to its position as a leader in the intelligent traffic management market and to helping solve some of the world’s most challenging surface transportation networks most popular related searches cloudbased analytical device weather information system weather prediction weather prediction model weather forecasting infrastructure modeling infrastruct